long_desc.thetext:
Hello,

If width, height and long text are set for tooltip then the text will come out of tooltip's borders in Firefox (tested for 2.0.0.8), Opera (tested for 9.24) and Safari (tested for 3.0.3). There is not such problem in IE 6. In IE 6 tooltip's text will be clipped.

Code snippet:

var btn = new qx.ui.form.Button("Test");
btn.set({
    left : 20,
    top : 20
});
var tip = new qx.ui.popup.ToolTip(qx.lang.String.pad("Message", 1000, " some text", true));
tip.set({
    width : "50%",
    height : "50%",
    showInterval : 100,
    hideInterval : 10000000
});
var lbl = tip.getAtom().getLabelObject();
lbl.set({
    wrap : true
});
btn.setToolTip(tip);
btn.addToDocument();
return;


Best regards,
Denis

Hi Denis!
Thank you for reporting this bug. As a workaround you can set "overflow" to "hidden". For your cnippet the code would be tip.setOverflow("hidden");
Note, that this change has some side effects (e.g. min-width will be disabled in Firefox) - that is the reason why we have not fixed the bug in this way...
